text.section:
An environmental covenant is perpetual unless it is:
By its terms, limited to a specific duration or terminated by the occurrence of a specific event;
Terminated by consent as provided under § 1-809 of this subtitle;
Terminated under subsection (b) of this section;
Terminated by foreclosure of an interest that has priority over the environmental covenant; or
Terminated or modified in an eminent domain proceeding, if:
The Agency that signed the covenant is a party to the proceeding;
Each person identified in § 1-809(a) and (b) of this subtitle is given notice of the pendency of the proceeding; and
The court determines, after a hearing, that the termination or modification will not adversely affect human health or the environment.
